WEBVTT

00:32.270 --> 00:32.900
Snap!

00:32.900 --> 00:33.700
-Oh!
-Oh!

00:33.700 --> 00:35.770
-Ah, she´s won.
-Hey, hey!

00:35.770 --> 00:37.070
Yeah, boy!

00:37.070 --> 00:39.330
Uh!
You fixed your cards!

00:39.330 --> 00:40.630
No, I haven´t.

00:40.630 --> 00:43.170
-You little cheat!
-No, I´m not!

00:43.170 --> 00:45.430
[ Indistinct shouting ]

00:45.430 --> 00:46.570
Missy!

00:46.570 --> 00:48.130
NANA: They say you don´t know
what you´ve got

00:48.130 --> 00:50.070
until it´s all gone.

00:50.070 --> 00:55.900
One day you´re mucking along,
taking it all for granted,

00:55.900 --> 00:59.030
and then the next thing
you know,

00:59.030 --> 01:01.500
everything changes.

01:06.670 --> 01:10.270
Did you not see those girls
checking you out at the gig?

01:10.270 --> 01:12.530
I´m serious.

01:13.700 --> 01:15.770
Well...

01:15.770 --> 01:18.670
I -- I didn´t notice
any of them.

01:18.670 --> 01:21.330
The only person I noticed
was you.

01:23.970 --> 01:26.670
[ Garbage can clatters ]

01:26.670 --> 01:28.970
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Boy laughs ]

01:28.970 --> 01:30.370
We can´t.

01:31.470 --> 01:32.430
Not here.

01:32.430 --> 01:35.930
Well, maybe next time
I can come back to yours.

01:36.900 --> 01:39.030
I´ll see you later.

01:39.030 --> 01:40.370
Bye.

01:40.370 --> 01:42.030
[ Car door closes ]

01:52.770 --> 01:54.900
IQBAL:
[ Clears throat ]

01:54.900 --> 01:56.730
Where have you been?

01:56.730 --> 02:01.330
[ Whispering ] I, um, had to go
around to Missy´s because,

02:01.330 --> 02:05.900
uh, she -- she had
lots of homework to do.

02:05.900 --> 02:07.270
Bed.

02:08.300 --> 02:09.770
Before you wake your mum up.

02:11.530 --> 02:12.930
Nas.

02:16.270 --> 02:18.300
I´m gonna need
an answer from you soon.

02:19.700 --> 02:21.900
I can´t -- I can´t do it.

02:23.470 --> 02:24.970
I´m sorry.

02:26.470 --> 02:27.970
Are you angry?

02:36.470 --> 02:38.100
[ Door opens ]

02:39.100 --> 02:40.130
[ Door closes ]

02:40.130 --> 02:43.170
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

02:43.170 --> 02:44.730
Ah!

02:55.300 --> 02:57.030
-Do you want strawberry jam?
-Yeah. But --

02:57.030 --> 02:58.530
Take the big bits out.
I know.

02:58.530 --> 02:59.700
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:01.500 --> 03:02.800
I´ve got to go.

03:02.800 --> 03:04.030
Aren´t you gonna
help me with Nana?

03:04.030 --> 03:06.100
What about your toast?

03:14.130 --> 03:16.230
Ready to go out now, Nana?

03:20.470 --> 03:22.700
Madam´s gone, so it´s just...

03:24.370 --> 03:25.370
[ Water dripping ]

03:46.670 --> 03:48.230
[ Indistinct talking continues ]

04:07.500 --> 04:08.930
NASREEN: Missy!

04:08.930 --> 04:11.700
Did you not hear me? I´ve
been calling you for ages.

04:11.700 --> 04:13.500
You all right?

04:13.500 --> 04:15.630
Um, Lila hasn´t texted me
since Friday,

04:15.630 --> 04:18.770
so I don´t know whether to text
or play it cool, you know?

04:20.270 --> 04:22.100
-Missy?
-Yeah.

04:22.100 --> 04:23.230
Right.

04:25.270 --> 04:27.470
[ Indistinct talking ]

04:40.730 --> 04:42.270
-Heya.
-Hey.

04:42.270 --> 04:43.930
You, uh, have a good weekend?

04:43.930 --> 04:45.270
Yeah, thanks.

04:45.270 --> 04:47.070
Do anything nice?

04:47.070 --> 04:49.270
Uh, I´m just -- sorry.

04:49.270 --> 04:52.270
Sure, sure.
See you in school.

05:01.770 --> 05:03.230
Jordan.

05:06.730 --> 05:08.270
I´ve got something for you.

05:10.530 --> 05:11.770
What do you want me
to do with this?

05:11.770 --> 05:14.730
You take a DNA swab
and you put it in his mouth.

05:14.730 --> 05:16.470
Yeah, I know to do with it,
Einstein.

05:16.470 --> 05:19.530
How can I get a swab
if she won´t let me see him?

05:19.530 --> 05:20.430
Good one.

05:25.030 --> 05:26.900
Oh, my God, look at that jacket.

05:26.900 --> 05:29.430
She looks dirty. She must´ve
copped that from a charity shop.

05:29.430 --> 05:31.030
[ Laughter ]

05:31.030 --> 05:33.470
Settle down, please, year 11.
Settle down.

05:33.470 --> 05:35.970
Phones away, girls.
Phones -- What´s so funny?

05:35.970 --> 05:37.430
Miley Cyrus, sir.

05:37.430 --> 05:38.370
Hey, don´t knock it.

05:38.370 --> 05:40.070
I had a jacket like that
back in the ´90s.

05:40.070 --> 05:41.100
Sir, you never.

05:41.100 --> 05:43.270
I did.
I had the curtains, as well.

05:43.270 --> 05:45.300
[ Laughter ]

05:45.300 --> 05:47.970
Oh, can me and Raz
go for pizza after school?

05:47.970 --> 05:50.530
I told Nana we´d make
"fadjitas," but they can wait.

05:50.530 --> 05:53.300
Peppers only repeat on me
anyway.

05:55.530 --> 05:56.900
Missy, are you all right?

06:00.170 --> 06:00.970
Missy!

06:00.970 --> 06:03.230
Yeah, go for it.
Have ham and pineapple for me.

06:03.230 --> 06:05.730
-Yes!
-Right, registration, please.

06:05.730 --> 06:07.970
-Tahira Abad.
-Yes, sir.

06:07.970 --> 06:10.500
-STEVE: Hayley Booth.
-Here, sir!

06:10.500 --> 06:13.300
-STEVE: Missy Booth.
-Yeah. Yes, sir.

06:14.700 --> 06:17.130
LILA: So you need to make sure
this is covered in your notes

06:17.130 --> 06:19.970
and that you have a labeled
diagram of the heart.

06:19.970 --> 06:23.170
Now, remember how the vena cava
looked and felt different

06:23.170 --> 06:25.470
to the aorta
in the heart we dissected?

06:25.470 --> 06:27.070
I like your bracelets, miss.

06:27.070 --> 06:28.570
LILA: My bracelets
are not gonna help you

06:28.570 --> 06:31.300
pass A-level biology, Shireen.

06:31.300 --> 06:33.970
Now, I want you to think about
the difference in pressure

06:33.970 --> 06:37.100
and how they have a different
structure to combat this.

06:37.100 --> 06:38.230
All right?

06:45.430 --> 06:47.170
Good work, Nas.

06:48.570 --> 06:51.330
Um, have you been talking
to Missy?

06:53.730 --> 06:55.900
She won´t say nothing.

06:55.900 --> 06:58.100
Yeah, ´cause she´s known
for keeping her mouth shut.

06:58.100 --> 07:00.200
[ Bell rings ]

07:00.200 --> 07:02.970
Right.
Finish this up for homework.

07:02.970 --> 07:06.900
I look forward to seeing your
perfect diagrams next class.

07:11.970 --> 07:14.670
Look, I´m sorry, okay?

07:14.670 --> 07:16.970
But this is a big deal for me
if it gets out.

07:16.970 --> 07:19.100
Look, this is a big deal
for me too.

07:25.900 --> 07:27.700
But, Mand, that´s the trouble.

07:27.700 --> 07:30.230
How can he get the test
if he can´t get near the baby?

07:30.230 --> 07:31.530
How is this your problem?

07:31.530 --> 07:33.430
Well, he´s got no one else
to fight for him, has he?

07:33.430 --> 07:35.170
It´s a bit above and beyond,
isn´t it?

07:35.170 --> 07:36.500
He´s really
turned the corner lately.

07:36.500 --> 07:37.470
He´s better behaved.

07:37.470 --> 07:39.470
He´s putting in the hours
in the rugby team.

07:39.470 --> 07:41.700
I just want to support him
so he keeps all that up.

07:41.700 --> 07:43.530
Leave it with me.
I´ll have a think.

07:44.770 --> 07:46.670
You all right?
How´s the team?

07:46.670 --> 07:47.900
Absolute shambles.

07:47.900 --> 07:49.700
But at least they´ve stopped
fighting each other,

07:49.700 --> 07:50.700
so that´s something.

07:50.700 --> 07:53.730
As long as they don´t completely
humiliate us against St. Mark´s.

07:53.730 --> 07:55.700
I´d rather encourage them
to do their best

07:55.700 --> 07:58.030
than focus on words
like "humiliate."

07:58.030 --> 08:01.500
Well, I think we should
always strive for excellence.

08:01.500 --> 08:03.400
Should we go through?

08:06.070 --> 08:07.330
Idiot.

08:10.230 --> 08:14.270
I don´t expect to find you
in detention

08:14.270 --> 08:15.900
when you´ve got rugby practice.

08:15.900 --> 08:19.370
Especially not with a brilliant
teacher like Miss Shariff.

08:19.370 --> 08:20.930
Uh, "Ms."

08:20.930 --> 08:23.230
It´s "Ms.," not "Miss."

08:23.230 --> 08:24.330
[ Boy laughs ]

08:24.330 --> 08:25.770
Sir, you just got told.

08:25.770 --> 08:27.670
Well, you can sit
and write a letter of apology

08:27.670 --> 08:29.770
to Ms. Shariff.

08:29.770 --> 08:31.430
I didn´t do anything, sir.

08:31.430 --> 08:33.970
Take a seat.
I´ll be with you in a minute.

08:43.970 --> 08:45.900
[ Indistinct talking ]

09:17.970 --> 09:19.270
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:28.270 --> 09:30.230
[ Exhales softly, sniffs ]

09:30.230 --> 09:31.700
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:44.130 --> 09:46.570
Okay, boys.
You can go now.

09:46.570 --> 09:49.630
Not till they´ve finished
their letters.

09:49.630 --> 09:52.300
No, it´s okay, Mr. Simpson.
Really.

09:52.300 --> 09:54.230
-Off you go.
-Thank you, miss.

09:54.230 --> 09:56.230
Okay, well, I don´t expect

09:56.230 --> 09:58.700
to see you back here again,
boys, okay?

10:02.630 --> 10:03.570
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:06.270 --> 10:08.130
-Nas.
-I´ve got to go.

10:08.130 --> 10:10.500
Missy just texted me.
She said it´s summat serious.

10:10.500 --> 10:11.130
Nas.

10:11.130 --> 10:13.170
I´m sorry, but I´ve got
to go see what´s wrong.

10:20.930 --> 10:24.270
Hi.
What´s happened?

10:25.370 --> 10:27.330
It´s Nana.

10:27.330 --> 10:28.570
She´s dead.

10:31.530 --> 10:33.970
We can´t tell anyone.
They´ll take Hayley into care.

10:44.500 --> 10:46.770
I don´t know what to do.

10:50.230 --> 10:54.230
Well, usually we´d have to
wash the body,

10:54.230 --> 10:57.270
but we don´t need to
worry about that.

10:57.270 --> 10:59.100
Maybe we should get her dressed.

10:59.100 --> 11:00.630
In her best clothes.

11:00.630 --> 11:02.970
She´s not going down bingo.

11:06.230 --> 11:08.970
Have you called the doctor?

11:08.970 --> 11:11.330
You do know you´re gonna
have to tell someone, right?

11:11.330 --> 11:13.900
-Say goodbye to Hayley.
-Aye.

11:17.730 --> 11:19.070
[ Line rings ]

11:22.970 --> 11:25.300
MAN: Good morning,
Ackley Bridge General Practice.

11:25.300 --> 11:27.770
Hello?

11:27.770 --> 11:31.730
I need to report a --
a death.

11:34.900 --> 11:37.130
-Will and Ms. Shariff?
-Yeah.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.430
He´s got it bad.

11:38.430 --> 11:42.100
-I can´t see her going for that.
-Why? He´s a good-looking lad.

11:42.100 --> 11:44.470
Do you, um,
think I´m getting fat?

11:44.470 --> 11:46.670
No.
You´ve still got it.

11:46.670 --> 11:48.630
-Team looks happy?
-Yeah.

11:48.630 --> 11:49.770
Apart from Jordan.

11:49.770 --> 11:52.500
Yes, I passed that on
to Candice´s social worker.

11:52.500 --> 11:54.100
She´s the one
with access to her,

11:54.100 --> 11:55.670
so, hopefully,
she´ll have a word.

11:55.670 --> 11:56.630
Oh, nice one.

12:00.970 --> 12:03.770
-What was that for?
-Do I need a reason?

12:08.270 --> 12:10.700
-Is it just you on your own?
-No, Mum´s out.

12:10.700 --> 12:12.570
She works shifts in a factory,

12:12.570 --> 12:14.300
making biscuits.

12:15.500 --> 12:18.370
I tried calling,
but couldn´t get through.

12:18.370 --> 12:19.330
No breaks.

12:19.330 --> 12:22.170
Practically slave labor,
but what can you do?

12:24.700 --> 12:27.170
-I´m sorry for your loss.
-Thank you, Doctor.

12:35.030 --> 12:37.170
Do you want to stay at mine?

12:38.530 --> 12:40.530
Hayley will be back soon.

12:40.530 --> 12:42.070
And your mum will be wondering
where you are.

12:42.070 --> 12:44.470
-Well, I can explain.
-No.

12:44.470 --> 12:47.900
The longer we keep this quiet,
the longer Hayley stays with me.

12:47.900 --> 12:49.070
Please, Nas.

12:54.500 --> 12:58.230
These bloody biscuits
broken already. Huh?

12:58.230 --> 13:00.630
-Are you deaf?
-Eh?

13:00.630 --> 13:02.700
This is because
Nas has come to her senses

13:02.700 --> 13:05.730
and said no
to your pendu friend, eh?

13:05.730 --> 13:08.030
Hey, what happened next door?

13:08.030 --> 13:09.730
Geeta says that she saw
Julie Booth

13:09.730 --> 13:10.900
taken out in a body bag.

13:10.900 --> 13:12.230
But you know Geeta.

13:12.230 --> 13:15.300
She say she saw Shilpa Shetty
down Lidl´s last week.

13:15.300 --> 13:17.570
IQBAL: What´s up
with the old cow, anyway?

13:19.500 --> 13:21.930
Oh, no.
She hasn´t?

13:22.900 --> 13:24.030
Ai Allah.

13:24.030 --> 13:26.370
Why didn´t you say?
You should´ve called me.

13:26.370 --> 13:28.630
I´ll go around
and check on the girls now.

13:28.630 --> 13:31.330
Go to the freezer and get
the kebabs and the choc ices.

13:31.330 --> 13:34.030
No, no, no, please. I told Missy
that I wouldn´t say anything.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.900
Why would you say such a thing?

13:35.900 --> 13:38.570
Mum, please,
you have to keep it a secret.

13:43.070 --> 13:44.430
[ Door opens ]

13:48.030 --> 13:49.570
Chloe´s such a bitch.

13:49.570 --> 13:51.900
Posting all this stuff
about haters online.

13:51.900 --> 13:53.630
It´s clearly about me and Raz.

13:53.630 --> 13:55.370
Where´s Nana?

13:55.370 --> 13:57.270
Hayley...

13:57.270 --> 13:59.430
She´s not rowing down at the
shops with Sajid again, is she?

13:59.430 --> 14:01.630
Always accusing him
of ripping her off.

14:01.630 --> 14:03.970
-It´s embarrassing.
-She had a heart attack.

14:06.070 --> 14:08.430
She died.

14:08.430 --> 14:10.700
No.

14:10.700 --> 14:12.630
-No, I don´t believe you!
-It´s okay.

14:12.630 --> 14:15.230
No, get off me!
No!

14:15.230 --> 14:16.900
I´m gonna look after us.
You and me.

14:16.900 --> 14:18.900
Just like it´s always been.

14:18.900 --> 14:20.170
[ Sobbing ]

14:23.030 --> 14:25.130
Where is she?

14:25.130 --> 14:27.070
They took her away.

14:28.930 --> 14:30.130
What about Mum?

14:36.730 --> 14:37.900
Have you not told her?

14:39.030 --> 14:40.330
What good would she be?

14:40.330 --> 14:43.630
-Missy.
-Tomorrow.

14:43.630 --> 14:45.430
She´ll be wasted by now.

14:46.370 --> 14:47.630
Listen...

14:51.230 --> 14:54.230
You´re not to mention this
to anyone, all right?

14:54.230 --> 14:56.930
-What about school?
-No one.

14:56.930 --> 15:00.300
You want to stay living here,
don´t you, with me?

15:01.600 --> 15:05.430
Then we have to carry on
like nothing´s happened.

15:05.430 --> 15:09.470
Get up every morning.

15:09.470 --> 15:11.430
Get ready for school.

15:11.430 --> 15:14.070
Have a laugh with your mates.

15:14.070 --> 15:16.530
Act like everything´s fine.

15:16.530 --> 15:19.030
We´ve just got to
keep it a secret.

15:19.030 --> 15:21.270
Until your birthday.

15:21.270 --> 15:23.030
Okay?

15:23.030 --> 15:24.130
[ Peeps ]

15:24.130 --> 15:25.500
Boys.

15:29.300 --> 15:29.930
[ Peeps ]

15:29.930 --> 15:31.270
Can we settle down please,
year 11,

15:31.270 --> 15:33.430
and get on with
the questions on the screen?

15:35.900 --> 15:37.730
Is there a problem, Hayley?

15:37.730 --> 15:39.630
-Get off!
-Shh!

15:42.500 --> 15:45.030
Do you want to explain to me
why you´ve done no work?

15:45.030 --> 15:47.500
No.

15:47.500 --> 15:49.570
Maybe you´ll find it easier
to work in isolation.

15:49.570 --> 15:51.500
Oh, whatever.

15:51.500 --> 15:52.700
Get off of me!

15:52.700 --> 15:54.500
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

15:54.500 --> 15:56.500
Right! Quiet!

16:04.330 --> 16:06.500
Not like you
to walk out of a lesson, Hayley.

16:06.500 --> 16:08.500
Is everything all right at home?

16:08.500 --> 16:10.130
Just don´t like her, miss.

16:10.130 --> 16:12.770
Don´t like her hair.
It annoys me.

16:14.470 --> 16:17.570
-Missy not in today?
-She´s off sick.

16:17.570 --> 16:19.070
Period pains.

16:34.330 --> 16:35.970
WOMAN:
For those on a tight budget,

16:35.970 --> 16:38.170
we´d recommend
our copper package.

16:38.170 --> 16:42.900
It´s a no-frills cremation
at 1,595.

16:42.900 --> 16:44.130
How much?

16:44.130 --> 16:48.730
It´s not including
third-party expenses.

16:48.730 --> 16:50.900
We can do a direct cremation --

16:50.900 --> 16:53.270
no ceremony, no mourners --

16:53.270 --> 16:54.900
at a reduced cost.

16:54.900 --> 16:56.670
How much is that?

16:56.670 --> 16:59.030
1,195.

16:59.030 --> 17:03.730
You shouldn´t be taking care
of all this yourself, love.

17:03.730 --> 17:05.730
What about your parents?

17:14.270 --> 17:15.500
[ Line ringing ]

17:18.700 --> 17:20.030
CANDICE: Jordan!

17:21.470 --> 17:22.900
Jordan!

17:22.900 --> 17:25.270
BOY: Oh, man,
look at the state of her.

17:25.270 --> 17:28.770
My dad´s had social services
on the phone all morning.

17:28.770 --> 17:31.500
-What are you playing at?
-All right, mate.

17:31.500 --> 17:33.100
Problem?!

17:33.100 --> 17:35.230
I thought I told you,
stay away.

17:35.230 --> 17:37.300
-Can I hold him?
-No.

17:37.300 --> 17:39.370
-Please?
-No!

17:39.370 --> 17:40.900
Hi, mate.

17:40.900 --> 17:44.770
Candice, what are you doing?
You can´t just walk into school.

17:44.770 --> 17:46.270
I´ll do what I like.

17:46.270 --> 17:49.170
Drop all this DNA crap. You´ll
have my brothers after you.

17:57.230 --> 18:00.170
Give me strength.
It´s actually quite clever.

18:00.170 --> 18:02.770
-I´ll see you later, then?
-Yeah, all right.

18:10.230 --> 18:12.730
Stroke of genius that, kid.

18:12.730 --> 18:14.630
Shouldn´t have to wait
too long.

18:18.530 --> 18:20.430
What if it´s not mine?

18:21.900 --> 18:23.370
Then you can move on.

18:24.570 --> 18:26.900
It´s always better
to know the truth, isn´t it?

18:28.770 --> 18:30.570
Come on.

18:33.500 --> 18:34.900
All right, Ms.?

18:34.900 --> 18:36.270
Hey.

18:36.270 --> 18:38.530
I´ve got something for you.

18:38.530 --> 18:39.900
Oh.

18:44.300 --> 18:46.300
Keep your blood-sugar levels up.

18:46.300 --> 18:48.130
Oh, uh...

18:48.130 --> 18:50.700
I can´t have this.

18:50.700 --> 18:52.900
I´m gluten intolerant.

18:52.900 --> 18:54.070
[ Sighs ]

18:54.070 --> 18:57.530
And I´m gay.

19:02.300 --> 19:03.430
All right.

19:06.370 --> 19:08.330
[ Sighs ]

19:09.030 --> 19:11.670
Will you send that
first class, please, Lozza?

19:11.670 --> 19:14.670
-What is it?
-A swab from a chlamydia test.

19:14.670 --> 19:17.270
I´m joking.
It´s a joke.

19:17.270 --> 19:19.630
Hey.
You all right, matey?

19:19.630 --> 19:21.230
It´s Lila.

19:21.230 --> 19:22.430
What, she got a boyfriend?

19:24.730 --> 19:25.970
She´s a lesbian.

19:29.230 --> 19:32.430
How was your date last week?

19:32.430 --> 19:33.730
With Sami?

19:33.730 --> 19:36.470
Oh, right. Yeah, I thought
there was a spark there.

19:36.470 --> 19:38.530
Turns out he´s engaged.

19:38.530 --> 19:41.100
Which is a shame

19:41.100 --> 19:43.970
because I could do with
a bit of romance right now.

19:43.970 --> 19:48.370
Yeah, well, not all hearts
and flowers where I´m standing.

19:50.570 --> 19:52.300
You ever tempted?

19:52.300 --> 19:54.900
What do you mean?

19:54.900 --> 19:56.900
You forget how long
I´ve known you.

19:56.900 --> 20:00.070
You might be head now, but I
remember when you were an NQT.

20:00.070 --> 20:01.630
Half-priced cocktails
on a Wednesday.

20:01.630 --> 20:03.670
-Don´t.
-[ Laughs ]

20:03.670 --> 20:04.900
You pulled that bloke,

20:04.900 --> 20:06.730
and he turned up next day
at parents evening.

20:06.730 --> 20:10.530
Aaron Sharp´s dad?
Oh, that was awful.

20:11.500 --> 20:14.330
Well, I admire you.

20:14.330 --> 20:15.930
Must be hard
to forgive and forget

20:15.930 --> 20:17.770
after what
Steve put you through.

20:22.070 --> 20:23.570
[ Door opens ]

20:25.030 --> 20:26.170
[ Door closes ]

20:30.900 --> 20:33.430
I´ll make us a brew.

20:33.430 --> 20:34.970
How did it happen?

20:38.770 --> 20:40.900
In the bath.
You´ve no milk.

20:42.670 --> 20:44.900
Don´t get benefits
till Thursday.

20:44.900 --> 20:46.970
Lend us a couple of quid?

20:53.570 --> 20:56.470
You´re a good kid, Missy.

20:56.470 --> 20:58.900
I´ve always said it.

20:58.900 --> 21:01.600
"My girl, Missy.

21:01.600 --> 21:02.970
She´s best."

21:05.700 --> 21:06.900
Bye, Mum.

21:06.900 --> 21:10.370
What´s going to happen
to the house?

21:10.370 --> 21:11.730
Me and Hayley
are stopping there,

21:11.730 --> 21:14.330
so don´t get any ideas
about selling it.

21:14.330 --> 21:15.970
I wouldn´t do that, love.

21:17.900 --> 21:19.900
I could move in.

21:19.900 --> 21:21.500
Look after you.

21:22.530 --> 21:24.030
Be a proper mum.

21:25.700 --> 21:27.670
No.

21:27.670 --> 21:30.030
I could cook.

21:30.030 --> 21:31.730
Chicken curry.

21:32.970 --> 21:34.230
You used to love that.

21:34.230 --> 21:37.170
Once!
You made it once!

21:44.770 --> 21:46.470
[ Indistinct talking ]

21:47.970 --> 21:51.370
-All right, miss?
-Morning, Zain.

21:58.900 --> 22:00.830
EMMA: I rolled over,
got an electric shock.

22:00.830 --> 22:02.430
Blue spark and everything.

22:02.430 --> 22:05.070
-You cheered up now, Hayley?
-CHLOE: Hey!

22:05.070 --> 22:06.530
It´s all right, Voyle.

22:06.530 --> 22:07.670
Say sorry, then.

22:07.670 --> 22:09.100
Get out of my face!

22:09.100 --> 22:10.270
I´m nowhere near
your ugly face.

22:10.270 --> 22:11.900
Leave her alone!

22:11.900 --> 22:13.300
Missy, don´t go
causing trouble now.

22:13.300 --> 22:15.770
-Let her go, Missy.
-She´s asking for a slap.

22:15.770 --> 22:16.900
Whatever she´s done,

22:16.900 --> 22:18.900
it´s not worth
getting yourself in trouble for.

22:21.270 --> 22:22.700
Go wait in my room, Missy.

22:22.700 --> 22:26.370
-She just threatened me!
-Don´t, Chlo.

22:26.370 --> 22:28.130
There´s summat going on
with those girls.

22:28.130 --> 22:30.230
They´re psychos?

22:30.230 --> 22:32.930
[ Boys laughing ]

22:36.070 --> 22:38.900
Nas, have you got a minute?

22:38.900 --> 22:40.470
MANDY:
Morning, Nasreen.

22:40.470 --> 22:44.130
Miss Shariff, can I have
a word with you in my office?

22:50.230 --> 22:51.170
[ Door closes ]

22:55.030 --> 22:56.770
I´ve been hearing
great things about you.

22:56.770 --> 23:01.100
Lots of girls enthusing about
science, which is brilliant.

23:02.170 --> 23:04.570
I hope you don´t mind
me bringing this up,

23:04.570 --> 23:06.230
but I thought you should know,

23:06.230 --> 23:07.900
school gossip
being what it is,

23:07.900 --> 23:12.770
that your sexuality
is causing quite a stir.

23:12.770 --> 23:16.030
I don´t see what business
that is of any--

23:16.030 --> 23:18.900
Nobody´s.
Nobody´s business but your own.

23:18.900 --> 23:20.900
And I hope
it goes without saying

23:20.900 --> 23:23.500
that homophobic bullying
of any kind

23:23.500 --> 23:25.700
will not be tolerated
here at Ackley Bridge.

23:25.700 --> 23:27.500
Good to know.

23:27.500 --> 23:32.070
I mean, part of me feels
that the more staff we have

23:32.070 --> 23:33.730
who are open
about this kind of thing,

23:33.730 --> 23:36.170
then the easier it will be
for any of our students

23:36.170 --> 23:38.100
who might be struggling
with coming out.

23:38.100 --> 23:40.300
So you don´t think
I should play it down?

23:40.300 --> 23:42.900
Well, uh...

23:44.030 --> 23:47.630
This is a tough place to put
your head above the parapet.

23:49.930 --> 23:53.030
I just wanted you to know
I´ve got your back.

23:54.570 --> 23:56.470
Thanks.

23:56.470 --> 23:59.230
What the bloody hell
are you doing?!

23:59.230 --> 24:01.970
Why are you behaving like this?

24:03.400 --> 24:06.100
-Are you gonna talk to me?
-Can you lend us a grand?

24:06.100 --> 24:07.900
What sort of trouble are you in?

24:07.900 --> 24:09.970
I´ve done nowt wrong.
I need it, that´s all.

24:09.970 --> 24:11.130
Can´t say why.

24:11.130 --> 24:14.570
I´m not lending you £1,000
without knowing what it´s for.

24:14.570 --> 24:15.900
You could lend it us?

24:17.470 --> 24:18.430
In theory.

24:21.230 --> 24:23.500
You´re not gonna tell me?
Well, I´m not gonna cough up.

24:23.500 --> 24:25.900
-We´re both busy people, so...
-Nana´s dead.

24:25.900 --> 24:28.030
She died two days ago.
Heart attack.

24:28.030 --> 24:30.700
Oh, Missy.

24:30.700 --> 24:31.900
I´m so sorry.

24:31.900 --> 24:33.570
Do you know what?
I´m all right.

24:33.570 --> 24:35.370
You´re in shock.

24:35.370 --> 24:38.070
She weren´t
in the greatest shape.

24:38.070 --> 24:39.900
Not that surprising, just...

24:39.900 --> 24:41.270
Wish she could have waited
a year.

24:41.270 --> 24:43.900
-A year?
-Till Hayley turned 16.

24:43.900 --> 24:45.970
Right.

24:49.900 --> 24:52.770
Are you gonna report it?

24:52.770 --> 24:55.900
I can hardly keep it a secret.

24:55.900 --> 24:57.730
Social services
don´t need to know!

24:57.730 --> 24:59.500
They´ll find out.

24:59.500 --> 25:01.170
Not yet.
Not if you don´t tell them.

25:01.170 --> 25:02.630
I can´t do that.

25:04.200 --> 25:06.370
They´ll split us up.
They´ll take Hayley into care.

25:06.370 --> 25:07.630
That doesn´t have to be
a bad thing.

25:09.270 --> 25:11.900
I´ve been looking after Hayley
for as long as I can remember.

25:11.900 --> 25:13.430
It´s been no different
now Nana´s gone.

25:13.430 --> 25:15.670
If anything,
it´ll be easier ´cause...

25:16.630 --> 25:19.900
´Cause she´s not there
to worry about.

25:19.900 --> 25:23.770
Remember what she were like in
year 8 when we got took off Mum?

25:23.770 --> 25:25.430
Now she´s lost Nana.

25:25.430 --> 25:28.100
She won´t be able to cope
with losing me too.

25:29.070 --> 25:31.370
Look, I know they´ll
find out in the end.

25:31.370 --> 25:33.430
But please, miss,

25:33.430 --> 25:36.270
let´s have some time
to get our heads ´round it.

25:36.270 --> 25:39.530
I can´t make any promises.

25:39.530 --> 25:42.470
But you´ll think about it?

25:53.770 --> 25:55.270
It´ll be tomorrow night,

25:55.270 --> 25:58.070
after hours,
probably about 6:00ish.

25:58.070 --> 26:00.500
Can me and me sister come?

26:00.500 --> 26:03.500
No family members, love.

26:03.500 --> 26:04.630
When do we get the ashes?

26:06.370 --> 26:08.270
Ashes will be another £100.

26:09.470 --> 26:11.330
Yeah, of course.

26:11.330 --> 26:13.430
Actually, I don´t think we´ll
bother, ´cause what´s the point?

26:13.430 --> 26:14.730
It´s not gonna bring her back,
is it?

26:14.730 --> 26:16.130
Right, well, thank you.

26:31.170 --> 26:32.900
She doesn´t look like one.

26:32.900 --> 26:34.900
ALYA: You can´t tell
from their clothes, stupid.

26:34.900 --> 26:36.130
Is there a problem, girls?

26:36.130 --> 26:38.030
-No, miss.
-Nothing.

26:38.030 --> 26:39.330
Miss, have you got a girlfriend?

26:39.330 --> 26:41.700
CORY: Shut up.
You´re an idiot.

26:42.900 --> 26:44.030
NEIL: Can I watch?

26:44.030 --> 26:45.900
JORDAN: For God´s sake,
what is wrong with you?

26:45.900 --> 26:47.100
You can go to isolation

26:47.100 --> 26:49.070
for making suggestive
and inappropriate comments

26:49.070 --> 26:49.900
to a member of staff.

26:49.900 --> 26:52.430
-Oh, come on, miss, why not?
-Eh, you can go as well.

26:52.430 --> 26:56.900
She´s made you look like a
right pair of mugs, hasn´t she?

27:02.970 --> 27:05.370
And, yeah, I´m gay.

27:05.370 --> 27:07.030
It´s not a big deal.

27:07.030 --> 27:08.730
And it´s none of your business.

27:10.970 --> 27:13.430
-Fair play to you, miss.
-Good for you, miss.

27:13.430 --> 27:14.970
[ Bell rings ]

27:18.730 --> 27:21.570
-See you later, miss.
-Bye, Shireen.

27:37.970 --> 27:39.900
It were that easy for you?

27:42.370 --> 27:45.070
It´s never going to be
that easy for me, though.

27:45.070 --> 27:47.900
-Nas...
-Maybe I should just do it?

27:47.900 --> 27:50.530
Maybe I should. You did,
and your world didn´t crumble.

27:50.530 --> 27:54.370
-Nasreen, listen, I...
-Then we could be together.

27:54.370 --> 27:57.170
Not here, obviously.
I´d have to change school.

27:57.170 --> 27:58.570
I´d have to go
to a different college.

27:58.570 --> 28:01.970
Look, it was stupid of me,
and wrong.

28:01.970 --> 28:04.800
I should never have let you
think that this could happen

28:04.800 --> 28:06.130
when it can´t.

28:06.130 --> 28:07.470
Nas, it can´t happen.

28:07.470 --> 28:09.930
Why?

28:09.930 --> 28:11.900
Why are you saying that?

28:11.900 --> 28:14.130
This can´t go any further.

28:16.700 --> 28:18.470
Please!

28:19.970 --> 28:22.900
But we´re good.
We could make it work.

28:22.900 --> 28:26.270
It´s school and family, but we
could just hack all that off.

28:26.270 --> 28:27.730
No, we can´t.

28:31.330 --> 28:32.570
Oh.

28:34.930 --> 28:38.730
Oh, it´s me that you
don´t want to be with?

28:41.900 --> 28:43.170
Sorry.

28:45.900 --> 28:47.230
Well...

28:50.270 --> 28:51.530
[ Door slams ]

28:53.630 --> 28:55.900
IQBAL: That teacher,
in front of all the kids?

28:55.900 --> 28:58.370
KANEEZ: She´s a grown woman.
She can do what she likes.

28:58.370 --> 29:00.230
Anyway, she´s from Glasgow,
innit?

29:00.230 --> 29:01.630
They´re different there.

29:01.630 --> 29:03.500
-Mum!
-Mm?

29:03.500 --> 29:05.900
Why do you two
have to be so small-minded?

29:05.900 --> 29:07.170
Don´t talk to us like that.

29:07.170 --> 29:09.100
We´re not your friends
in the street.

29:09.100 --> 29:10.230
Show some respect.

29:10.230 --> 29:13.030
Respect?
You want to talk about respect?

29:13.030 --> 29:15.100
You´ve just been slagging off
Miss Shariff for coming out!

29:15.100 --> 29:17.100
She´s fine with it.
We´re fine with it.

29:17.100 --> 29:18.700
It´s the 21st century
in England.

29:18.700 --> 29:20.070
I think
everyone´s fine with it.

29:20.070 --> 29:22.230
I´ve got nothing against it,
love.

29:22.230 --> 29:25.700
We´ve got gay girls in Pakistan.
We just don´t go on about it.

29:25.700 --> 29:28.570
You lot shouldn´t have to
hear about her private life.

29:28.570 --> 29:30.530
Private life?
Right, okay.

29:30.530 --> 29:32.430
So you´re saying that
Mr. Bell and Miss Carter

29:32.430 --> 29:33.930
shouldn´t come out
as being married?

29:33.930 --> 29:35.900
Oh, no, it´s different for them,
isn´t it,

29:35.900 --> 29:37.070
because they´re straight.

29:37.070 --> 29:38.700
Or is it just because
Miss Shariff is Asian

29:38.700 --> 29:39.900
and they´re not?

29:39.900 --> 29:41.730
Because I feel like
it´s one rule for them

29:41.730 --> 29:43.030
and another for us!

29:43.030 --> 29:45.100
What is wrong with you?

29:46.270 --> 29:48.770
[ Speaks Punjabi ]

29:51.130 --> 29:53.730
-[ Door opens ]
-[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

29:55.230 --> 29:56.630
What are you doing here?

29:59.170 --> 30:00.470
What´s she doing here?

30:00.470 --> 30:03.630
You´re not supposed to
see us without supervision.

30:03.630 --> 30:06.470
Better call social services,
then.

30:12.130 --> 30:13.900
You robbing...

30:13.900 --> 30:15.300
-That´s mine.
-Get out!

30:15.300 --> 30:16.270
Don´t!

30:16.270 --> 30:17.770
She made it for me
when I were a baby.

30:17.770 --> 30:21.900
And when you were born,
she passed it down.

30:21.900 --> 30:23.770
It´s the only thing
I´ve got left of her.

30:23.770 --> 30:26.770
You were a crap daughter
and a worse mum.

30:26.770 --> 30:28.470
-Missy!
-She´ll only sell it!

30:28.470 --> 30:30.970
You heartless cow.
You´re as bad as she were.

30:33.630 --> 30:34.700
Now look what you´ve done!

30:34.700 --> 30:36.470
Aah! Get out!

30:36.470 --> 30:38.570
-Get out!
-Aah!

30:38.570 --> 30:39.900
-Get off me!
-Get out!

30:39.900 --> 30:42.900
MISSY: You´re poison!
I´ll kill you!

30:42.900 --> 30:44.270
Stay away from us!

30:44.270 --> 30:45.300
[ Screaming ]

30:45.300 --> 30:46.900
What are you doing?!

30:46.900 --> 30:48.730
HAYLEY: Stop!

30:48.730 --> 30:50.900
Missy, get off!

30:50.900 --> 30:52.630
-Missy, stop!
-Somebody help me!

30:52.630 --> 30:54.070
-Stop it!
-Stay away from us!

30:54.070 --> 30:56.170
-Get out!
-You´re so selfish!

30:56.170 --> 30:57.900
She were my mum!

30:59.330 --> 31:00.570
Now where am I gonna go?

31:01.830 --> 31:04.930
I only ever wanted
what were best for you girls.

31:08.670 --> 31:10.270
We´re better off without her.

31:10.270 --> 31:13.430
I wish it were you that died!

31:13.430 --> 31:15.030
What are
you all looking at, huh?!

31:15.030 --> 31:16.570
[ Shouting in Punjabi ]

31:28.300 --> 31:30.430
[ Sobbing ]

31:44.900 --> 31:46.770
Can I get in bed with you?

31:56.170 --> 31:57.700
I´m sorry.

32:02.300 --> 32:04.030
You knew
and you didn´t tell me?

32:04.030 --> 32:05.900
What, are you trying to
get my school shut down?

32:05.900 --> 32:07.330
Oh, your school now.

32:07.330 --> 32:08.700
Is this about you or the Booths?

32:08.700 --> 32:10.130
She were only trying to help.

32:10.130 --> 32:12.100
Have you any idea
what you have done?

32:12.100 --> 32:14.300
This is
a serious safeguarding issue.

32:14.300 --> 32:16.630
We´ve got two at-risk
children left on their own.

32:16.630 --> 32:17.930
Well, one, technically.

32:17.930 --> 32:20.530
You could get fired.

32:20.530 --> 32:23.230
We could have Ofsted
breathing down our necks.

32:23.230 --> 32:25.570
It´s lucky Mrs. Paracha told me.

32:25.570 --> 32:26.930
I´m gonna have to call
child protection.

32:26.930 --> 32:28.300
-EMMA: Wait.
-KANEEZ: No!

32:28.300 --> 32:31.070
They´re like family to me.
They´re not in any danger.

32:31.070 --> 32:32.700
It´s the cremation tonight.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.500
Will you just hold off
until then?

32:34.500 --> 32:36.900
Please?

32:42.930 --> 32:45.270
That´s completely inappropriate.

32:49.930 --> 32:50.930
You okay?

32:51.930 --> 32:53.300
Yeah.

32:55.130 --> 32:56.730
Do you want to borrow summat
of mine?

32:58.730 --> 33:00.970
I´ve just had a better idea.

33:28.170 --> 33:31.330
Do you -- Do you have these
in any other sizes?

33:31.330 --> 33:34.730
WOMAN: Yes, there´s
an extra small and a small.

33:37.900 --> 33:39.170
Thanks.

33:45.430 --> 33:47.500
-[ Laughter ]
-Where have you been?

33:47.500 --> 33:48.670
It´s time to go.

33:48.670 --> 33:50.070
Well...

33:52.330 --> 33:53.370
What do you reckon?

33:53.370 --> 33:55.570
-Where´d you get them from?
-[ Knock on door ]

33:56.530 --> 33:57.770
No, don´t.

34:07.630 --> 34:09.270
Thought you might want a lift.

34:14.230 --> 34:16.470
Can you take this tag out?
It´s digging in my back.

34:16.470 --> 34:18.970
Can´t.
I´m taking them back tomorrow.

34:18.970 --> 34:20.930
We´re only borrowing them.

34:20.930 --> 34:22.730
We´re not thieves, Hayley.

34:23.700 --> 34:26.770
Missy´s right.
You don´t want any more trouble.

34:29.570 --> 34:31.500
HAYLEY:
Is that smoke Nana?

34:31.500 --> 34:33.030
NASREEN: Yeah.

34:33.030 --> 34:34.900
Did she have a favorite poem?

34:34.900 --> 34:36.770
She liked "Bat Out of Hell."

34:53.730 --> 34:56.470
There you go.
Thank you.

35:03.770 --> 35:07.270
I thought you needed
cheering up.

35:07.270 --> 35:09.900
You´re a good friend
to Missy, Nas.

35:09.900 --> 35:11.670
I´m proud of you.

35:11.670 --> 35:12.970
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

35:16.470 --> 35:17.730
What is it?

35:17.730 --> 35:20.300
Some lad?

35:20.300 --> 35:21.730
You can tell me.

35:21.730 --> 35:24.770
Whoever he is,
you´re worth ten of him.

35:24.770 --> 35:28.670
This is why
sensible Pakistani girls

35:28.670 --> 35:32.900
get their dads to vet
suitable husbands for them.

35:34.330 --> 35:38.630
I´m joking, kid.
You can do what you like.

35:38.630 --> 35:40.900
I´m not gonna force you
into anything.

35:40.900 --> 35:44.170
Just option´s there
if you want it. That´s all.

35:44.170 --> 35:46.570
I know, but I don´t want it.

35:46.570 --> 35:50.270
You always were a free spirit.

35:50.270 --> 35:59.900
I used to tell your mum not to
be so strict with you, but...

35:59.900 --> 36:02.770
I don´t want you
to limit your options.

36:02.770 --> 36:07.970
But think -- What is really
here for you in Ackley Bridge?

36:07.970 --> 36:10.470
So, what´s he like, then,

36:10.470 --> 36:11.970
this lad?

36:17.470 --> 36:19.330
[ Indistinct talking ]

36:30.100 --> 36:32.270
You were up and out early
this morning.

36:32.270 --> 36:34.370
How else am I supposed to
get this lot match fit, eh?

36:34.370 --> 36:36.970
Thank you.
For everything you´re doing.

36:39.030 --> 36:42.970
STEVE: All right, come on, lads.
Get in.

36:42.970 --> 36:45.900
Lively, lively, lively.
Come on.

36:52.930 --> 36:55.470
-What are you looking at?
-You got jam on your chops.

36:55.470 --> 36:57.170
-Get off.
-[ Laughs ]

36:57.170 --> 37:00.700
Morning, girls.
Miss Carter wants to see you.

37:00.700 --> 37:02.100
Come through.

37:19.130 --> 37:21.330
I know it sounds drastic,

37:21.330 --> 37:22.970
but we can´t leave you
on your own.

37:22.970 --> 37:25.030
It´s not safe.

37:25.030 --> 37:27.500
Now, we found Hayley
a lovely foster family.

37:27.500 --> 37:28.970
She´s got a family -- me.

37:28.970 --> 37:32.270
Nobody´s saying
you haven´t coped admirably.

37:32.270 --> 37:34.370
But you shouldn´t have to,
Missy.

37:34.370 --> 37:37.300
And I know it´s hard,

37:37.300 --> 37:39.770
but the two of you can see
each other every weekend.

37:39.770 --> 37:41.900
What about at school?

37:50.170 --> 37:52.330
The foster family
are in Bradford.

37:52.330 --> 37:54.070
They´re the closest ones
available.

37:54.070 --> 37:55.970
Look, I´m so sorry.

37:55.970 --> 37:58.230
We´ll do all we can to find
one here, but until then...

37:58.230 --> 37:59.370
Did you know about this?

37:59.370 --> 38:01.330
Not till last night.

38:01.330 --> 38:03.300
You knew last night?

38:03.300 --> 38:05.530
Look, it isn´t ideal,
but there´s no other option.

38:05.530 --> 38:07.070
You´ll have to
get through me first!

38:07.070 --> 38:09.370
MANDY: Missy, we do understand
how painful this is for you,

38:09.370 --> 38:11.700
but it has got to happen.

38:11.700 --> 38:12.770
If you keep obstructing,

38:12.770 --> 38:14.230
I´m gonna have to ask you
to leave the room.

38:14.230 --> 38:15.370
She´s my sister!

38:15.370 --> 38:17.270
MANDY: And don´t you want
what´s best for her?

38:17.270 --> 38:19.430
Missy, this is a good family.

38:19.430 --> 38:22.970
They´ve been fostering
for years.

38:22.970 --> 38:24.170
Be honest.

38:24.170 --> 38:26.070
Are you stopping her
from leaving

38:26.070 --> 38:27.530
for your benefit or for hers?

38:27.530 --> 38:29.530
You can say what you like,
I´m not going!

38:29.530 --> 38:30.900
Hey, hey, hey.

38:38.970 --> 38:41.930
Go on, Hayley. [ Sniffles ]
I´ll see you every weekend.

38:41.930 --> 38:43.970
-No!
-Just go!

38:43.970 --> 38:45.430
The sooner we do this,
the better.

38:45.430 --> 38:46.470
-I´m not going!
-Just go!

38:46.470 --> 38:48.470
I don´t want to
look after you anyway!

38:51.070 --> 38:53.270
[ Door opens ]

38:53.270 --> 38:54.300
[ Door closes ]

39:01.230 --> 39:03.300
[ Sobs ]

39:03.300 --> 39:05.030
[ Down-tempo piano music
playing ]

39:08.470 --> 39:10.170
[ Crying ] I´m gonna
call you every day.

39:10.170 --> 39:12.030
[ Music continues ]

39:40.630 --> 39:42.570
-Are you all right?
-Get off me!

40:29.700 --> 40:31.900
-[ Sighs ]
-Hey.

40:31.900 --> 40:33.730
-[ Sobs ]
-Aw...

40:35.070 --> 40:37.570
Hey, I know it can´t
have been easy, love, but...

40:37.570 --> 40:39.300
[ Sobbing ]

40:41.100 --> 40:45.330
It was a tough decision, but
it wasn´t the wrong decision.

40:45.330 --> 40:47.700
If you´d left them on their own
and something would´ve happened,

40:47.700 --> 40:50.670
you´d never forgive yourself.

40:51.630 --> 40:53.230
Hey. Come on.

40:54.900 --> 40:57.900
Come on.
I´ll, um, get us a takeaway.

40:57.900 --> 40:59.970
I´ll, uh --
I´ll miss the match tonight

40:59.970 --> 41:02.730
so you can watch
"America´s Next Top Model."

41:02.730 --> 41:04.530
I´m a classy guy.

41:09.300 --> 41:12.670
-I don´t deserve you.
-[ Laughs ]

41:12.670 --> 41:15.170
I think we both know
that I´m the one

41:15.170 --> 41:17.100
that´s punching
above the weight here.

41:23.300 --> 41:24.270
[ Clears throat ]

41:25.170 --> 41:26.530
[ Sighs ]

41:31.100 --> 41:32.730
I slept with Sadiq.

41:32.730 --> 41:33.970
[ Sobs ]

41:40.430 --> 41:42.370
I´m sorry.

41:42.370 --> 41:44.170
I´m so sorry.

41:48.500 --> 41:50.130
It was once.
It was just the once.

41:50.130 --> 41:53.570
And I have regretted it
ever since.

42:04.330 --> 42:06.630
[ Sighs ]

42:10.900 --> 42:13.330
I said...

42:13.330 --> 42:15.630
We can get through this.

42:15.630 --> 42:17.430
We can.

42:17.430 --> 42:20.470
No, I-I don´t --
I don´t think we can.

42:20.470 --> 42:21.630
We can.

42:21.630 --> 42:23.570
We got over Claire.
I got over Claire.

42:23.570 --> 42:25.270
I got over you having a baby
with someone else.

42:25.270 --> 42:26.970
Is that what this is? Revenge?
Is that what it is?

42:26.970 --> 42:28.230
Because it´s not
the same, Mandy.

42:28.230 --> 42:29.970
No, because what you did
was a lot worse.

42:29.970 --> 42:33.630
What are you talking about?
I have to see him every day!

42:33.630 --> 42:36.170
I have to see you two
together every day,

42:36.170 --> 42:39.500
knowing that his hands
have been all over you.

42:39.500 --> 42:42.030
You make me sick.

42:44.330 --> 42:45.900
[ Sobbing ]

42:49.470 --> 42:51.700
[ Down-tempo instrumental music
plays ]

42:55.700 --> 42:57.470
NANA: Like I say,

42:57.470 --> 43:01.330
you don´t know what you´ve got
until it´s gone.

43:01.330 --> 43:03.100
[ Knock on door ]

43:03.100 --> 43:07.470
All them little moments
you took for granted,

43:07.470 --> 43:13.070
all the people you thought
would be there for you forever.

43:13.070 --> 43:14.300
[ Knock on door ]

43:16.470 --> 43:21.970
Believe me,
they can all go in a heartbeat.

43:31.330 --> 43:34.470
So hold on to it while you can.

43:35.970 --> 43:38.500
Hold on to anything good.

44:48.100 --> 44:49.170
[ Laughter ]

44:49.170 --> 44:50.900
Look at my face!

44:50.900 --> 44:52.100
Look at you!

44:52.100 --> 44:53.070
I´m drumming.

44:53.070 --> 44:55.470
[ Laughter ]
